flavor_text_entries.gold:
It swings its long
snout around play­
fully, but because it is so strong,
that can be dan­
gerous.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
As a sign of af­
fection, it bumps
with its snout. However, it is so
strong, it may
send you flying.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
During the desert­
ed morning hours,
it comes ashore where it deftly
uses its trunk to
take a shower.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
For its nest, PHANPY digs a vertical pit 
in the ground at the edge of a river.
It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that
the area has been claimed.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
PHANPY uses its long nose to shower
itself. When others gather around, they
thoroughly douse each other with water. These POKéMON can be seen drying their
soaking-wet bodies at the edge of
water.
flavor_text_entries.emerald:
PHANPY’s big ears serve as broad fans.
When it becomes hot, it flaps the ears
busily to cool down. Even the young are
very strong.
flavor_text_entries.firered:

snout. However, it is so strong, it may
send you flying.
flavor_text_entries.leafgreen:
It swings its long snout around playfully,
but because it is so strong, this can be
dangerous.
flavor_text_entries.diamond:
It is strong despite its compact
size. It can easily pick up and
carry an adult human on its back.
